TWC WIOA Monthly Training Activity Report

Participant Name: Theodore Lawrence
Training Provider: Cloud Technology Experts
Training Program: Cloud/DevOps Engineering
Reporting Month: January 2026
Instructor: Dr. Damian Igbe, PhD
Submitted To: Ms. Crystal Norwood

Week of January 10, 2026
Training Focus: Linux Package Management & System Administration

During this week, training focused on Ubuntu Linux fundamentals with emphasis on package management using APT. Instruction covered command syntax, troubleshooting errors, updating repositories, installing and removing software packages, cleaning cached files and unused dependencies, and managing services using systemctl. Additional concepts included command piping with grep and understanding localhost networking behavior. Hands-on exercises reinforced full package lifecycle management and service verification.

Week of January 17, 2026
Training Focus: AWS Troubleshooting, DNS, Load Balancing & HTTPS Security

This week emphasized real-world AWS infrastructure troubleshooting, including EC2 connectivity validation, Route 53 DNS configuration, Application Load Balancer target health analysis, and removal of misconfigured resources. Training included creation of hosted zone records, domain-to-load balancer mapping, and SSL certificate implementation using AWS Certificate Manager to enable HTTPS traffic. Practical exercises reinforced systematic diagnostics and secure cloud architecture design.

Week of January 24, 2026
Training Focus: AWS Storage Services & S3 Static Website Hosting

During this week, training centered on Elastic Block Store (EBS) volume creation and integration with EC2 instances, including disk partitioning, formatting, mounting, and persistent data verification. Instruction also covered AWS S3 static website configuration, troubleshooting access permissions, and applying bucket policies for public access. These activities reinforced cloud storage administration and secure content hosting.

Week of January 31, 2026
Training Focus: Networking Fundamentals & AWS VPC Architecture

The final week of January focused on foundational networking concepts using the OSI Reference Model and TCP/IP communication principles. Training concluded with hands-on creation of AWS Virtual Private Cloud (VPC) environments, including CIDR planning, public and private subnet segmentation, route table configuration, and Internet Gateway implementation. Practical validation exercises reinforced secure and scalable cloud network design.

